line_1: Since (tho' he seems to Lose) He surely Wins,
line_2: Who gives but earthly Comforts for his Sins.

line_1: His watery way with waving volutes wins,
line_2: Or listening librates on unmoving fins.

line_1: Oft high in heaven the hissing Demon wins
line_2: His towering course, upborne on winnowing fins;

line_1: With playful charms her hoary lover wins,
line_2: And wields his trident, — while the Monarch spins.

line_1: That ev'ry grant sincere affection wins,
line_2: And where our wants have end, our love begins.
